def: Taught by practice or by repeated observations; skillful orwise by means of trials, use, or observation; as, an experiencedphysician, workman, soldier; an experienced eye.The ablest and most experienced statesmen. Bancroft.
In the manner of a gerund; as, or in place of, a gerund.
An excessive devotion to the interests of the sacerdotal order;undue influence of the clergy; sacerdotalism.
A species of mixed action, which lies for the recovery ofpossession of real property, and damages and costs for the wrongfulwithholding of it. Wharton.
The quality of being a baby; the personality of an infant.
Disposed or arranged by an action originating in one's self orin itself.These molecular blocks of salt are self-posited. Tyndall.

An unsymmetrical, divalent, hydrocarbon radical, C2H4 metamericwith ethylene but written thus, CH3.CH to distinguish it from thesymmetrical ethylene, CH2.CH2. Its compounds are derived fromaldehyde. Formerly called also ethidene.

The quality or state of being unable; lack of ability; want ofsufficient power, strength, resources, or capacity.It is not from an inability to discover what they ought to do, thatmen err in practice. Blair.
